The above cases illustrate the unscrupulous use made of these letters which were one of the sore abuses with which the curia afflicted Europe. The popes were constautly complaining cf them and threatening punishments, but never applied the only remedy of refusing to issue them. They seem to have been sold without scruple to all purchasers and were a source os profit to the vendors which no pope was hardy enough to suppress.
